025/**
026 * Allows the definition of input and output data types.
027 *
028 * <p>
029 * The Schema Object allows the definition of input and output data types for Swagger 2.0, including objects,
030 * primitives, and arrays. This object is an extended subset of the JSON Schema Specification Draft 4, with
031 * additional extensions provided by the Swagger Specification to allow for more complete documentation.
032 *
033 * <h5 class='section'>Swagger Specification:</h5>
034 * <p>
035 * The Schema Object supports all properties from JSON Schema Draft 4, including but not limited to:
036 * <ul class='spaced-list'>
037 *    <li><c>type</c> (string) - The data type. Values: <js>"string"</js>, <js>"number"</js>, <js>"integer"</js>, <js>"boolean"</js>, <js>"array"</js>, <js>"object"</js>, <js>"file"</js>
038 *    <li><c>format</c> (string) - The format modifier (e.g., <js>"int32"</js>, <js>"int64"</js>, <js>"float"</js>, <js>"double"</js>, <js>"date"</js>, <js>"date-time"</js>)
039 *    <li><c>title</c> (string) - A short title for the schema
040 *    <li><c>description</c> (string) - A description of the schema
041 *    <li><c>default</c> (any) - The default value
042 *    <li><c>multipleOf</c> (number) - Must be a multiple of this value
043 *    <li><c>maximum</c> (number) - Maximum value (inclusive by default)
044 *    <li><c>exclusiveMaximum</c> (boolean) - If true, maximum is exclusive
045 *    <li><c>minimum</c> (number) - Minimum value (inclusive by default)
046 *    <li><c>exclusiveMinimum</c> (boolean) - If true, minimum is exclusive
047 *    <li><c>maxLength</c> (integer) - Maximum string length
048 *    <li><c>minLength</c> (integer) - Minimum string length
049 *    <li><c>pattern</c> (string) - Regular expression pattern the string must match
050 *    <li><c>maxItems</c> (integer) - Maximum array length
051 *    <li><c>minItems</c> (integer) - Minimum array length
052 *    <li><c>uniqueItems</c> (boolean) - If true, array items must be unique
053 *    <li><c>maxProperties</c> (integer) - Maximum number of object properties
054 *    <li><c>minProperties</c> (integer) - Minimum number of object properties
055 *    <li><c>required</c> (array of string) - Required property names
056 *    <li><c>enum</c> (array) - Possible values for this schema
057 *    <li><c>properties</c> (map of {@link SchemaInfo}) - Object property definitions
058 *    <li><c>items</c> ({@link Items}) - Schema for array items
059 *    <li><c>allOf</c> (array of {@link SchemaInfo}) - Must validate against all schemas
060 *    <li><c>discriminator</c> (string) - Property name for polymorphism (Swagger extension)
061 *    <li><c>readOnly</c> (boolean) - Relevant only for Schema properties (Swagger extension)
062 *    <li><c>xml</c> ({@link Xml}) - XML representation details (Swagger extension)
063 *    <li><c>externalDocs</c> ({@link ExternalDocumentation}) - Additional external documentation (Swagger extension)
064 *    <li><c>example</c> (any) - Example value (Swagger extension)
065 * </ul>
066 *
067 * <h5 class='section'>Example:</h5>
068 * <p class='bjava'>
069 *    <jc>// Construct using SwaggerBuilder.</jc>
070 *    SchemaInfo <jv>info</jv> = <jsm>schemaInfo</jsm>()
071 *       .type(<js>"string"</js>)
072 *       .title(<js>"foo"</js>)
073 *
074 *    <jc>// Serialize using JsonSerializer.</jc>
075 *    String <jv>json</jv> = Json.<jsm>from</jsm>(<jv>info</jv>);
076 *
077 *    <jc>// Or just use toString() which does the same as above.</jc>
078 *    <jv>json</jv> = <jv>info</jv>.toString();
079 * </p>
080 * <p class='bjson'>
081 *    <jc>// Output</jc>
082 *    {
083 *       <js>"type"</js>: <js>"string"</js>,
084 *       <js>"title"</js>: <js>"foo"</js>
085 *    }
086 * </p>
087 *
088 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
089 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://swagger.io/specification/v2/#schema-object">Swagger 2.0 Specification &gt; Schema Object</a>
090 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://swagger.io/docs/specification/2-0/data-models/">Swagger Data Models</a>
091 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://json-schema.org/">JSON Schema Specification</a>
092 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanSwagger2">juneau-bean-swagger-v2</a>
093 * </ul>
094 */
095public class SchemaInfo extends SwaggerElement {
096
097   private String
098      format,
099      title,
100      description,
101      pattern,
102      type,
103      discriminator,
104      ref;
105   private Number
106      multipleOf,
107      maximum,
108      minimum;
109   private Integer
110      maxLength,
111      minLength,
112      maxItems,
113      minItems,
114      maxProperties,
115      minProperties;
116   private Boolean
117      exclusiveMaximum,
118      exclusiveMinimum,
119      uniqueItems,
120      readOnly,
121      required;
122   private Object
123      _default,  // NOSONAR - Intentional naming.
124      example;
125   private Items items;
126   private Xml xml;
127   private ExternalDocumentation externalDocs;
128   private Set<Object> _enum;  // NOSONAR - Intentional naming.
129   private Set<SchemaInfo> allOf;
130   private Set<String>
131      requiredProperties;
132   private Map<String,SchemaInfo> properties;
133   private SchemaInfo additionalProperties;
134
135   /**
136    * Default constructor.
137    */
138   public SchemaInfo() {}
139
140   /**
141    * Copy constructor.
142    *
143    * @param copyFrom The object to copy.
144    */
145   public SchemaInfo(SchemaInfo copyFrom) {
146      super(copyFrom);
147
148      this.additionalProperties = copyFrom.additionalProperties == null ? null : copyFrom.additionalProperties.copy();
149      this.allOf = copyOf(copyFrom.allOf);
150      this._default = copyFrom._default;
151      this.description = copyFrom.description;
152      this.discriminator = copyFrom.discriminator;
153      this._enum = copyOf(copyFrom._enum);
154      this.example = copyFrom.example;
155      this.exclusiveMaximum = copyFrom.exclusiveMaximum;
156      this.exclusiveMinimum = copyFrom.exclusiveMinimum;
157      this.externalDocs = copyFrom.externalDocs == null ? null : copyFrom.externalDocs.copy();
158      this.format = copyFrom.format;
159      this.items = copyFrom.items == null ? null : copyFrom.items.copy();
160      this.maximum = copyFrom.maximum;
161      this.maxItems = copyFrom.maxItems;
162      this.maxLength = copyFrom.maxLength;
163      this.maxProperties = copyFrom.maxProperties;
164      this.minimum = copyFrom.minimum;
165      this.minItems = copyFrom.minItems;
166      this.minLength = copyFrom.minLength;
167      this.minProperties = copyFrom.minProperties;
168      this.multipleOf = copyFrom.multipleOf;
169      this.pattern = copyFrom.pattern;
170      this.readOnly = copyFrom.readOnly;
171      this.ref = copyFrom.ref;
172      this.required = copyFrom.required;
173      this.requiredProperties = copyOf(copyFrom.requiredProperties);
174      this.title = copyFrom.title;
175      this.type = copyFrom.type;
176      this.uniqueItems = copyFrom.uniqueItems;
177      this.xml = copyFrom.xml == null ? null : copyFrom.xml.copy();
178      this.properties = copyOf(copyFrom.properties, SchemaInfo::copy);
179   }
180
181   /**
182    * Make a deep copy of this object.
183    *
184    * @return A deep copy of this object.
185    */
186   public SchemaInfo copy() {
187      return new SchemaInfo(this);
188   }

1183   /**
1184    * Resolves any <js>"$ref"</js> attributes in this element.
1185    *
1186    * @param swagger The swagger document containing the definitions.
1187    * @param refStack Keeps track of previously-visited references so that we don't cause recursive loops.
1188    * @param maxDepth
1189    *    The maximum depth to resolve references.
1190    *    <br>After that level is reached, <c>$ref</c> references will be left alone.
1191    *    <br>Useful if you have very complex models and you don't want your swagger page to be overly-complex.
1192    * @return
1193    *    This object with references resolved.
1194    *    <br>May or may not be the same object.
1195    */
1196   public SchemaInfo resolveRefs(Swagger swagger, Deque<String> refStack, int maxDepth) {
1197
1198      if (ref != null) {
1199         if (refStack.contains(ref) || refStack.size() >= maxDepth)
1200            return this;
1201         refStack.addLast(ref);
1202         var r = swagger.findRef(ref, SchemaInfo.class).resolveRefs(swagger, refStack, maxDepth);
1203         refStack.removeLast();
1204         return r;
1205      }
1206
1207      if (items != null)
1208         items = items.resolveRefs(swagger, refStack, maxDepth);
1209
1210      if (properties != null)
1211         properties.entrySet().forEach(x -> x.setValue(x.getValue().resolveRefs(swagger, refStack, maxDepth)));
1212
1213      if (additionalProperties != null)
1214         additionalProperties = additionalProperties.resolveRefs(swagger, refStack, maxDepth);
1215
1216      this.example = null;
1217
1218      return this;
1219   }
